Academy.Description: The taskmasters of the Legion's academies train the elite Legionnaires to reinforce the ranks and bring defeat to the enemy.
Academy.Name: Academy

Armory.Description: Although the Legion always possesses basic armaments for its soldiers, the armory provides more complex ranged weapons and battlefield supplies.
Armory.Name: Armory

ArrowTower.Description: The most accurate but weakest of the Legion's defenses, arrow towers fling forth a constant barrage of arrows against approaching foes.
ArrowTower.Name: Arrow Tower

CannonTower.Description: More powerful than their arrow-spitting counterparts, cannon towers fling flaming orbs that explode, damaging any caught in the blast.
CannonTower.Name: Cannon Tower

CharmShrine.Description: The holy charm shrines glow with the light of ancient crystals and potent magic, summoning the elemental forces of the Tempests and awakening the mighty Behemoths.
CharmShrine.Name: Charm Shrine

ChlorophilicSpire.Description: Weaving its roots around the nearby living structures of the Beast Horde, chlorophilic spires draw energy from the sun and use it to heal damaged buildings.
ChlorophilicSpire.Name: Chloro Spire

EntangleSpire.Description: The static charge spire collects and stores electrical energy and then violently unleashes it onto nearby enemies.
EntangleSpire.Name: Static Spire

Garrison.Description: Though not as sturdy as strongholds, garrisons play the same role, supplying soldiers on the front line of battle.
Garrison.Name: Garrison

GroveMine.Description: The enchanted trees of mine groves employ their roots to draw forth gold from the earth, spilling the Mother's bounty from their boughs.
GroveMine.Name: Mine Grove

HumanHellShrine.Description: Once a hell shrine is built atop the lingering wound of a Scar, enemy souls can be sacrificed in order to unleash Hellbourne warriors onto the battlefield.
HumanHellShrine.Name: Hell Shrine

Lair.Description: Sacred lairs are the spiritual center of any gathering of the Beast Horde, brining forth warriors and furnishing healing and supplies to carry on the struggle.
Lair.Name: Lair

Monastery.Description: Monasteries are home to Chaplains, who tend the spiritual needs of the Legion's forces. These halls hold many enchantments yet be discovered, given enough time and resources.
Monastery.Name: Monastery

Nexus.Description: The soulstones of the nexus are the Horde's mystical link to the power of the Mother, and provide mystic powers to augment the natural weapons of Beast warriors.
Nexus.Name: Nexus

PredatorDen.Description: Carved in the aspect of terrible stone maws, predator dens are the breeding grounds for some of the Horde's most deadly warriors.
PredatorDen.Name: Predator Den

Sanctuary.Description: Sanctuaries provide a training ground for the Horde's Shamans, and within its shadows they come to grasp the powers the Mother has bestowed upon them.
Sanctuary.Name: Sanctuary

ShieldTower.Description: Shield towers radiate an aura of protection that protects nearby structures from harm.
ShieldTower.Name: Shield Tower

SiegeWorkshop.Description: Siege workshops are the model of human industry, filled with the hurly-burly of invention and engineering. Within its walls, the Legion builds its steambuchets and battering rams.
SiegeWorkshop.Name: Siege Workshop

SteamMine.Description: Harnessing the power of flame and water, steam mines are filled with pneumatic drills that bring forth gold from the earth.
SteamMine.Name: Steam Mine

StrataSpire.Description: Strata spires harness the power of the wind to hurl frozen bolts at their foes.
StrataSpire.Name: Strata Spire

Stronghold.Description: At the heart of a territory controlled by the Legion is a stronghold, and its loss spells doom. Within its walls the Legion of Man finds peace and some measure of security.
Stronghold.Name: Stronghold

SubLair.Description: Sub lairs are practical structures meant to bring Beasts closer to their enemies and grant them relief from the battlefront.
SubLair.Name: Sub Lair

AdvancedSights.Description: Using this advanced scope gives a 25%% bonus to damage dealt with ranged weapons. Does not grant ability to zoom.
AdvancedSights.Name: Advanced Sights

AmmoPack.Description: Allows the unit to carry 70%% more ammunition for ranged weaponry.
AmmoPack.Name: Ammo Pack

AmmoSatchel.Description: Allows the unit to carry 35%% more ammunition for ranged weaponry.
AmmoSatchel.Name: Ammo Satchel

Chainmail.Description: Using woven steel, this armor provides an additional 3 armor rating.
Chainmail.Name: Chainmail

GustOfWind.Description: You can charge for 30%% longer and are immune to ranged damage while charging or dodging.
GustOfWind.Name: Gust of Wind

HealthMajor.Description: Restores 200 health immediately, but has a 5 second cooldown whenever you are struck.
HealthMajor.Name: Major Health Potion

HealthMinor.Description: Restores 100 health immediately, but has a 5 second cooldown whenever you are struck.
HealthMinor.Name: Minor Health Potion

HealthReplenish.Description: Restores 125 health over 15 seconds but is cancelled if you take damage.
HealthReplenish.Name: Replenish Potion

HealthShrine.Description: Places a Health Shrine down that restores 15 hitpoints per second to nearby allied units over 12 seconds.
HealthShrine.Name: Health Shrine

LynxFeet.Description: This special item enchants its bearer's paws, granting 35%% faster movement speed for 15 seconds. If damage is taken the speed boost is removed.
LynxFeet.Name: Lynx Feet

MagicAmplifier.Description: This trinket amplifies magic damage, giving a 25%% increase to damage dealt with ranged weapons.
MagicAmplifier.Name: Magic Amplifier

MalikenBrain.Description: The brain of Maliken. When you receive a soul you will restore 70 mana.
MalikenBrain.Name: Brain of Maliken

MalikenHeart.Description: The heart of Maliken. When you receive a soul you will restore 50 health.
MalikenHeart.Name: Heart of Maliken

MalikenLungs.Description: The lungs of Maliken. When you receive a soul you will restore 150 stamina and receive a temporary 15%% increase in movement speed.
MalikenLungs.Name: Lungs of Maliken

MalikenSoul.Description: Maliken is no longer available to action players.
MalikenSoul.Name: Soul of Maliken

ManaCrystal.Description: Ranged weaponry costs 40%% less mana to use.
ManaCrystal.Name: Mana Crystal

ManaShrine.Description: Places a Mana Shrine down that restores 15 mana per second to nearby allied units over 10 seconds.
ManaShrine.Name: Mana Shrine

ManaStone.Description: Ranged weaponry costs 25%% less mana to use.
ManaStone.Name: Mana Stone

Platemail.Description: Using heavy, solid metal, this armor increases armor rating by 6 but slows movement speed by 5%%.
Platemail.Name: Platemail

PowerAbsorption.Description: This item will absorb one negative effect on your character per 45 seconds, removing the harmful effect from your character and restoring 100 mana. Can only absorb dispellable negative effects.
PowerAbsorption.Name: Power Absorption

SavioursValor.Description: Activating this item will cast recall on your player and allow you to return to the spawn screen. If you take damage while waiting to be recalled, the recall effect will be cancelled.
SavioursValor.Name: Savior's Valor

ShieldOfWisdom.Description: Upon use, Shield of Wisdom will spend the rest of your remaining mana, and create a shield that will absorb incoming damage. The more mana drained by Shield of Wisdom, the tougher the damage shield.
ShieldOfWisdom.Name: Shield of Wisdom

SpeedBoost.Description: These boots allow their bearer to gain 35%% faster movement speed for 15 seconds. If damage is taken the speed boost is removed.
SpeedBoost.Name: Speed Boost

StoneHide.Description: The Stone Hide item transforms the bearer's hide, providing 6 additional armor but decreasing movement speed by 5%%.
StoneHide.Name: Stone Hide

TokenOfLife.Description: Activating this item will resurrect you. Simply activate the item at the death screen to use it.
TokenOfLife.Name: Token of Life

ToughSkin.Description: This item increases the strength and thickness of beast skin, giving those who wear it 3 additional armor.
ToughSkin.Name: Tough Skin

TrinketOfRestoration.Description: On activation, this item will restore 75 health for yourself and nearby allies, as well as provide an armor buff of 5 for 15 seconds.
TrinketOfRestoration.Name: Trinket of Restoration

Chest.Description: This chest holds something of value.
Chest.Name: Treasure Chest

AmmoDepot.Description: This is a small resupply center that can be used to help continue forward progress on the battlefield.
AmmoDepot.GameTip: Press 'E' to reload your ammo supply
AmmoDepot.Name: Ammo Depot

BeastSpawnPortal.Description: Officers can summon a magical portal to allow fellow squadmates to quickly join the battlefront.
BeastSpawnPortal.Name: Spawn Portal

DemoCharge.Description: Using specific chemicals, alchemists from the Capital City have devised a compact explosive used to level buildings.
DemoCharge.Name: Demo Charge

ElectricEye.Description: This magical eye detects enemies in a radius and identifies them with a red beam.
ElectricEye.Name: Electric Eye

HealingWard.Description: Increases nearby ally unit's health regeneration by 10 hp per second and mana regenaration by 6 per second.
HealingWard.Name: Ward of Life

HealthShrine.Description: Restores 15 health per second for 12 seconds in an area.
HealthShrine.Name: Health Shrine

HumanOfficerSpawnFlag.Description: A magical portal capturing the power of Sol that allows squadmates to instantly spawn from its location.
HumanOfficerSpawnFlag.Name: Spawn Portal

ManaFountain.Description: The conjurer summons a fountain whose enchanted waters recover the power of magic for all who drink from it.
ManaFountain.Name: Mana Fountain

ManaShrine.Description: Restores 15 mana per second for 10 seconds in an area.
ManaShrine.Name: Mana Shrine

ManaWard.Description: Increases nearby ally unit's mana regeneration by 10 mana per second.
ManaWard.Name: Arcane Ward

Sentry.Description: The Hunter calls fourth a bat to recon the battlefield as well as identify hidden units.
Sentry.Name: Sentry Bat

ShieldGenerator.Description: This small contraption generates an electromagnetic field that deflects all projectiles for 30 seconds.
ShieldGenerator.Name: Shield Generator

SteamTurret.Description: A portable mini tower, powered by steam, that shoots fragments of metal.
SteamTurret.Name: Steam Turret

Venus.Description: A plant deployed by the conjurer used to damage enemies with its poisonous spore projectiles.
Venus.Name: Poisonous Venus

Blaze.Description: From the burning rage welling up from within their hearts, predators can summon forth fireballs to fling at their foes from afar.
Blaze.Name: Blaze

Crossbow.Description: A relic from before the Age of Enlightenment, the Crossbow has shorter range and does only modest damage compared to modern weapons.
Crossbow.Name: Crossbow

Exorcise.Description: A massive direct damage spell that can only be cast upon Hellbourne units.
Exorcise.Name: Exorcise

Fireball.Description: Using a magically imbued rock that explodes on impact, this weapon is great for dealing damage to large groups and buildings.
Fireball.Name: Fireball

FrostBolts.Description: A basic magical spell, but one of great use, Frost Bolts shoot forth at great speed, freezing enemies and impeding their progress.
FrostBolts.Name: Frost Bolts

HolyBolt.Description: The first cantrip in the Chaplain catechism teaches how to expel a holy bolt that not only wounds its foe, but sprays forth holy fire when it strikes a target.
HolyBolt.Name: Holy Bolt

Launcher.Description: More accurate and powerful than the grenade launcher, rocket launchers are the peak of human light ordnance and the mark of a well-equipped Legionnaire.
Launcher.Name: Rocket Launcher

Lightning.Description: By channeling the same energies that enable them to transform their bodies, Shapeshifters can call down a lightning strike from the sky to char their foes.
Lightning.Name: Lightning Strike

Locusts.Description: Through a mystical process, Summoners can create special pheremones that summon a frantic swarm of Locusts to harry and annoy enemies.
Locusts.Name: Locusts

Mortar.Description: A combination of alchemic mystery and mechanical brilliance, grenade launchers blast glass orbs filled with explosive concoctions into enemy ranks.
Mortar.Name: Grenade Launcher

Ravager.Description: Cruder than other modern weapons, the ravager discharges a steady but haphazard stream of heated shrapnel from it's gaping maws.
Ravager.Name: Ravager

Repeater.Description: Complex instruments of gears and springs, repeaters are technological marvels to the uneducated savages, who take visceral pleasure in the rapid spray of iron that the weapon produces.
Repeater.Name: Repeater

Rifle.Description: A simple gas-powered firearm with a high rate of fire, these rifles prove that even lowly laborers can become lethal marksmen when the need arises.
Rifle.Name: Semi-Auto Rifle

RottenFlesh.Description: Using extra body parts, the devourer is capable of launching the guts and innards of his foes back at his enemies.
RottenFlesh.Name: Gut Launcher

Scorch.Description: Calling fourth hellfire, the Revenant sends scorching lava at his enemies, causing immediate damage and burning them over time.
Scorch.Name: Scorch

Shotgun.Description: When indiscriminate iron shards are better than a well-placed shot, builders turn to their scatterguns and put on a grim smile.
Shotgun.Name: Scattergun

SniperBow.Description: The marksman's bow is of ancient design and requires extraordinary skill, launching arrows with incredible accuracy and power. Blocking while wielding this bow will allow you to zoom in.
SniperBow.Name: Marksmans Bow

StaticDischarge.Description: Calling upon the power of the storm, the Shapeshifter summons electricity through his body to damage his foes.
StaticDischarge.Name: Static Discharge

Venom.Description: Demonstrating that they are as much flora as fauna, conjurers can eject venomous spores from their arms to poison enemies from a distance.
Venom.Name: Venomous Spore

BatteringRam.Description: The battering ram slams a behemoth skull into enemy buildings, reducing them to rubble.
BatteringRam.Name: Ram

BattleAxe.Description: The slow, steady reaping of a Legionnaire's massive battle axe is a fearsome sight to behold.
BattleAxe.Name: Battle Axe

Broadswords.Description: In each hand, battle-hardened Savages wield deadly longswords, each heavier than any normal man could bear to lift and each sharpened for lethal effect.
Broadswords.Name: Broadswords

Cleaver.Description: Forged in the very fires of hell, the devourer's Iron Cleaver is a weapon to be feared.
Cleaver.Name: Iron Cleaver

ConjurerClaws.Description: Though conjurers are gentle creatures when tending to nature, they are equipped with sharp claws capable of rending human flesh at the least provocation.
ConjurerClaws.Name: Thorned Claws

FlameSword.Description: Enormous and wrapped in fire, the flame sword of a Malphas is the symbol of its power and a tool of terrible destruction. No mortal blade can match its mettle.
FlameSword.Name: Flame Sword

Hammer.Description: With an iron hammer and a strong arm, builders can smash more than just rocks, keeping lesser Beasts at bay.
Hammer.Name: Iron Hammer

HellStaff.Description: Each Revenant wields a burning hell staff, forged in demonic infernos and capable of inflicting burning agony on any mortal flesh it touches.
HellStaff.Name: Hell Staff

MalikenBlade.Description: The blade of the almighty maliken. Strong attacking with this blade will throw it, strong attack again to teleport to it.
MalikenBlade.Name: Blade of Damnation

PredatorClaws.Description: The vicious claws of the predator tear through enemy armor and flesh alike, making this Beast one of the most powerful warriors.
PredatorClaws.Name: Bone Claws

Push.Description: With a strong gust of wind, a tempest can push back any approaching foes and keep them at a safe distance.
Push.Name: Pushback

ShifterClaws.Description: Relying on their quick fists and natural strength, Shapeshifters are able to defend themselves with reasonable success against those who attack them.
ShifterClaws.Name: Shifter Claws

ShortBlades.Description: The twin blades Scouts wield are honed sharper than a razor's edge and make for deadly work at close range.
ShortBlades.Name: Short Blades

SpiritHammer.Description: Though primarily dedicated to the mystic arts, a Shaman also bears a huge war hammer for crushing the skulls of those who would defile the Earth Mother.
SpiritHammer.Name: Spirit Hammer

Staff.Description: Although Chaplains' magical staves are made for better work than mere melee attacks, when the situation demands it they can be used to drive off weaker foes.
Staff.Name: Staff of Sol

SummonerStaff.Description: The seemingly ornamental spikes on a Summoner's staff enable it to become a serviceable weapon when the situation demands it, as more than a few humans have learned to their peril.
SummonerStaff.Name: Enchanting Staff

Tree.Description: Wielding an enormous uprooted tree the way a man might handle a cudgel, Behemoths crush any enemy or building in their path.
Tree.Name: Tree Trunk

Wings.Description: The Hunter's wings provide more than just maneuverability on the battlefield. When confronted, the Hunter can use his wings as mighty weapons.
Wings.Name: Bat Claws

BatteringRam.Description: From time immemorial, Man has knocked things down with Battering Rams. But times have changed. The Legion's new Rams are driven by steam engines and protected by gouts of flame. And mounted upon each Ram's steel-bound central log is the unbreakable skull of a Behemoth, mocking the Beasts even as it razes their homes.
BatteringRam.Name: Battering Ram

Bearloth.Description: A hybrid of several different species, this familiar uses brute strength to pound the summoner's enemies into the ground.
Bearloth.Name: Bearloth

BeastWorker.Description: Before the young Saplings mature to become full fledged combat ready Conjurers, they hone their skills of nature as workers for battle Commanders.
BeastWorker.Name: Sapling

Behemoth.Description: Earth-shakers and wall-breakers, Behemoths march across the battlefield wielding uprooted trees with deadly force. The sheer force of their attacks brings enemies to their knees, where powerful blows make short work of them. Of all the creatures in the Beast Horde, none inspires such fear in Man as the Behemoth.
Behemoth.Name: Behemoth

Chaplain.Description: It is in service to Sol, Father of Light, that Chaplains take up their holy staves and heed the call to battle. From their faith comes the power to heal friend and destroy foe, and the curses called down by Chaplains can make even a Behemoth fall before a humble warrior. Even death itself is no barrier to their magic, for Chaplains may raise fallen comrades or cast Hellbourne back from whence they came.
Chaplain.Name: Chaplain

Conjurer.Description: Formed from earth and plant alike, Conjurers are able to call upon nature to create, protect, and mend the structures necessary for the growth of the Horde. This same spiritual gift allows Conjurers to launch magical attacks against those who threaten them or their work.
Conjurer.Name: Conjurer

Devourer.Description: Sewn together from the corpses of fallen warriors, the Devourer strikes both fear and disgust into the hearts of all who oppose him.
Devourer.Name: Devourer

Engineer.Description: No mere peons in the human society, Builders are instead the very backbone of the Legion of Man. All the works of Man are built by the iron hammer and strong will of these stolid workers. Moreover, their ability to mend siege weapons and deploy supplies at forward locations makes them invaluable.
Engineer.Name: Builder

HumanWorker.Description: Volunteers from the lesser skilled Engineers from the Capital City are sent to the battle front to do Commanders bidding.
HumanWorker.Name: Journeyman

Imp.Description: The most basic of familiars, it's weak appearance belies the arcane powers it controls at it's fingertips.
Imp.Name: Imp

Legionnaire.Description: Legionnaires, the namesakes of the Legion of Man, bring unflinching power to the battlefield. Whether cleaving bloody swaths through enemy ranks with their massive battle-axes or blasting orbs of scalding alchemic concoctions, Legionnaires spread carnage among their foes. The steady pounding of their march across the plain is a sound of joy for friends and terror for foes.
Legionnaire.Name: Legionnaire

Malphas.Description: Bone, fire, and hatred compose the Malphai, lieutenants among Hell's host and scourges of the living. Armored against all manner of attack and wreathed with smoke and the stench of brimstone, these giants are the bane of the living races of Newerth. Few who have faced their burning swords have lived to tell the tale.
Malphas.Name: Malphas

Marksman.Description: Trained since youth to be swift, silent, and deadly, Scouts spend much of their lives deep in the wild, apart from their brethren. Though many view them as aloof, none doubt the importance of Scouts in the war against the Beasts, as the countless enemy corpses, dead by a single blow, attest.
Marksman.Name: Marksman

Predator.Description: The core of the Beast Horde, bred for battle and hungry for human blood, are Predators. Fueled by rage, these beasts rend their enemies with huge bone claws--often laced with poison--and devour their very flesh. With their speed and savage attacks, Predators have spread terror through the Legion of Man.
Predator.Name: Predator

Revenant.Description: Cobbled from the bones and armor of fallen warriors, Revenants are bound together by their burning hatred of all life. The souls of the fallen fuel the flames of their sorcery, and through this dark magic the Revenants spread desolation across Newerth and feed ever more corpses into the pits of Hell.
Revenant.Name: Revenant

Savage.Description: The brute warriors of the Legion of Man, Savages are dedicated to the rush of battle and the thrill of bloodlust. Armed with a pair of battle-notched blades and quick-firing bows, Savages rush heedless into battle, inspiring their comrades to similar feats of heroism. The life of a Savage is often short and glorious.
Savage.Name: Savage

Shaman.Description: First awakened to the ways of the Mother and mighty in her service are the Shamans. Even as they crush their foes with their enormous war-hammers, Shamans are a balm to their allies, healing and even resurrecting those who have fallen in battle. Moreover, these proud and solemn priests bear the magical essence of the Mother with them, empowering others around them to mystical feats.
Shaman.Name: Shaman

ShapeShifter.Description: In the dark recesses beneath the earth, where shadows and nightmares breed, the Beast Horde found the furtive and deadly Shape Shifters. With absolute mastery of their own essence, Shape Shifters take not just the lives of their enemies but even their forms. In the face of defeat, Shape Shifters let go of their essence altogether and leave the world in a blaze of destruction.
ShapeShifter.Name: Shape Shifter

Steambuchet.Description: The apex of Man's ingenuity is the Steambuchet. Filled with every spring, sprocket, gear, and gasket imaginable and powered by an enormous boiler, the Steambuchet trundles across the battlefield flinging enormous boulders or fireballs at the enemy. Any foe foolish enough to be caught in the way of its blasts finds a quick death, and even sturdy buildings fall before its onslaught.
Steambuchet.Name: Steambuchet

Summoner.Description: Summoners bring not only themselves to battle but also their company of locusts, imps, and fearsome bearloths. Through ancient arcane powers that evolved during the Fall, Summoners have the power not only to gather these creatures but also to calm other animals and monsters they find across Newerth.
Summoner.Name: Summoner

Tempest.Description: Spirits born of the elements, Tempests howl across the land raining fire and ice alike, indeed even calling great meteors from the heavens. These ethereal beings change with will into their ethereal forms, untouchable by mortal weapons. Even among the Horde, these strange beings are viewed with awe bordering on fear.
Tempest.Name: Tempest

BatteringRam.Description: From time immemorial, Man has knocked things down with Battering Rams. But times have changed. The Legion's new Rams are driven by steam engines and protected by gouts of flame. And mounted upon each Ram's steel-bound central log is the unbreakable skull of a Behemoth, mocking the Beasts even as it razes their homes.
BatteringRam.Name: Battering Ram

Behemoth.Name: Behemoth

Even death itself is no barrier to their magic, for Chaplains may raise fallen comrades or cast Hellbourne back from whence they came.
Chaplain.Name: Chaplain

Conjurer.Name: Conjurer

Devourer.Name: Devourer

All the works of Man are built by the iron hammer and strong will of these stolid workers. Moreover, their ability to mend siege weapons and deploy supplies at forward locations makes them invaluable.
Engineer.Name: Builder

Hunter.Description: Mostly nocturnal creatures, the Hunter is most at home when stalking his prey on the battlefield
Hunter.Name: Hunter

Legionnaire.Description: Legionnaires, the namesakes of the Legion of Man, bring unflinching power to the battlefield. Whether cleaving bloody swaths through enemy ranks with their massive battle-axes or blasting orbs of scalding alchemic concoctions, Legionnaires spread carnage among their foes. The steady pounding of their march across the plain is a sound of joy for friends and terror for foes.
Legionnaire.Name: Legionnaire

Maliken.Description: Maliken Grimm, the fallen human king who brought the Hellbourne back in the world. This unit could be summoned by combining his heart, lungs, brains and soul. He is no longer available.
Maliken.Name: Maliken

Few who have faced their burning swords have lived to tell the tale.
Malphas.Name: Malphas

The life of a Savage is often short and glorious.
Savage.Name: Savage

Moreover, these proud and solemn priests bear the magical essence of the Mother with them, empowering others around them to mystical feats.
Shaman.Name: Shaman

In the face of defeat, Shape Shifters let go of their essence altogether and leave the world in a blaze of destruction.
ShapeShifter.Name: Shape Shifter

Filled with every spring, sprocket, gear, and gasket imaginable and powered by an enormous boiler, the Steambuchet trundles across the battlefield flinging enormous boulders or fireballs at the enemy buildings. Blocking while using this unit will increase your field of view.
Steambuchet.Name: Steambuchet

Summoner.Description: Summoners bring not only themselves to battle but also their company of locusts, imps, and fearsome bearloths. They are no longer available.
Summoner.Name: Summoner

Tempest.Description: Spirits born of the elements, Tempests howl across the land raining fire and ice alike, indeed even calling great meteors from the heavens. These ethereal beings change with will into their ethereal forms, untouchable by mortal weapons. Blocking while using this unit will increase your field of view.
Tempest.Name: Tempest

BuilderGrenade.Description: High splash damage chemically filled glass spheres
BuilderGrenade.Name: NAME

Grenade.Description: High splash damage chemically filled glass spheres
Grenade.Name: NAME

Scorch.Description: Calling forth the fires of Hell, Revenants spray forth burning destruction to Scorch their enemies' bodies or buildings.
Scorch.Name: NAME

Mine.Description: Build Steam Mines or Mine Groves upon these mines to extract gold.
Mine.Name: Gold Mine

Scar.Description: Though protected by daemonic guardians eager to feed their undying hunger for mortal suffering, Scars are sought after as sites on which to build Sacrificial Shrines.
Scar.Name: Scar

FireBombardment.Description: Requiring great build-up of steam and flames in the boiler, a Fire Bombardment nevertheless unleashes a devastating, explosive attack that makes up for any delay.
FireBombardment.Name: Fire Bombardment

StoneBombardment.Description: With a gasp of steam and the crack of iron cables, Steambuchets launch a Stone Bombardment with surprising speed to rain damage upon enemy buildings and warriors alike.
StoneBombardment.Name: Stone Bombardment

AmmoDepot.Description: Gadget: Deploys an ammo depot for 30 seconds which allies can use to completely restock their ammo supplies. The builder who places the ammo depot is awarded 25 experience per player who refills their ammo.
AmmoDepot.Name: Supply Depot

BackStab.Description: Instant: A powerful attack that deals 115 to 140 damage to opponents from the front, or 230-280 damage if you strike from behind your opponent.
BackStab.Name: Backstab

Bash.Description: Instant: Bash the opponent with your battle-axe, stunning them for 0.6 seconds and doing 80-100 damage.
Bash.Name: Bash

BeastBuild.Description: Instant: When no commander is present, this skill grants access to the build menu, allowing conjurers to build any structure of the Beast horde.
BeastBuild.Name: Build

BladeFrenzy.Description: Instant: Sends Maliken into a blade frenzy. This ability does damage to all nearby enemies as maliken moves around at a reduced speed. Based on which melee mode is active, the frenzy will have different effects
BladeFrenzy.Name: Blade Frenzy

Blind.Description: Instant: Sprays acid at opponents within melee range. The acid blocks their vision and disables their skills for 2.5 seconds, deals 75 damage, and reduces their armor and movement speed by 20%%.
Blind.Name: Acid Spray

Build.Description: Instant: When no commander is present, this skill grants access to the construction menu, allowing engineers to build any structure of the Legion of Man.
Build.Name: Build

Burrow.Description: Naturally subterranean creatures, Shapeshifters can quickly Burrow beneath the ground and thus avoid detection until the moment is ripe to emerge once more.
Burrow.Name: Burrow

Carnivorous.Description: Instant: For 15 seconds, 22.5%% of the damage you deal with melee attacks is returned to you as health.
Carnivorous.Name: Carnivorous

Cheetah.Description: Channeling: Activates the shapeshifter's cheetah form at the cost of 5 mana per second. In this form the shapeshifter's movement speed is at 140%% of normal. While in cheetah form, all other skills and abilities are disabled.
Cheetah.Name: Cheetah Form

CriticalStrike.Description: Instant: A quick melee strike, dealing 20 damage instantly then another 84 damage over 6 seconds. The bleeding target's speed is reduced by 25%%.
CriticalStrike.Name: Critical Strike

DemoCharge.Description: Gadget: Places an explosive with a 16 second fuse. When the fuse reaches zero, the demo charge explodes doing 1600 base damage to structures in a small radius. Damage done will change depending on the building's armor.
DemoCharge.Name: Alchemic Bundle

Disembark.Description: Instant: Self-destructs your siege unit, freeing you from the driver's seat.
Disembark.Name: Disembark

DoubleSwing.Description: Instant: An melee attack using both of the savage's blades. Deals 90-115 damage and stuns for 0.75 seconds.
DoubleSwing.Name: Double Swing

ElectricEye.Description: Gadget: Places an Electric Eye on the ground that lasts for 5 minutes and reveals enemy units, including ones who are polymorphed or cloaked. The user is rewarded with experience for how effective the eye is at scouting the battlefield.
ElectricEye.Name: Eye

Enrage.Description: Instant: Enrages the predator for 15 seconds, reducing his armor by 50%% and increasing his damage dealth by 25%%.
Enrage.Name: Enraged Frenzy

Ethereal.Description: Channeling: Activates ethereal form for 10 mana per second. In ethereal form, the Tempest cannot receive damage, but moves at reduced speed and cannot summon meteors. Ethereal form can stay active for a maximum of 25 seconds
Ethereal.Name: Ethereal State

Flames.Description: Instant: Sprays flames around the battering ram for 5 seconds. Enemy units caught in the flames take 55 damage per second for 3.5 seconds.
Flames.Name: Protective Flames

Frenzy.Description: Instant: When activated, each successful melee strike will increase the hunter's movement speed by 20%% for 2.5 seconds. Costs 4 mana per second to stay active.
Frenzy.Name: Frenzy

HealingWard.Description: Channeling: Activates a healing aura around the shaman for a cost of 5 mana per second. Units within this aura regenerate an additional 10 health per second and 6 mana per second.
HealingWard.Name: Chant of Restoration

HumanOfficerPortal.Description: Gadget: Allows a Squad's Officer to drop a portal giving his Squadmates a new spawn location at its location.
HumanOfficerPortal.Name: Portal of Sol

HunterVenomous.Description: Self Buff: The hunter releases poison within his wings. Each melee attack also poisons the target for 5.5 seconds, doing 2 damage per second. The poison effect will stack with each successful melee hit. Costs 4 mana per second to stay active.
HunterVenomous.Name: Venemous

LogSweep.Description: Used to disable nearby foes, the Behemoth uses his uprooted tree to knockdown enemies in its path.
LogSweep.Name: Log Sweep

ManaWard.Description: Channeling: Activates an arcane aura around the shaman at the cost of 6 mana per second. Other units in this aura will regenerate an addition 6 mana per second.
ManaWard.Name: Arcane Chant

Morale.Description: Instant: Boosts the morale of the savage for 30 seconds, increasing health regeneration by 50%%, mana regeneration by 200%% and stamina regeneration by 40%%.
Morale.Name: Morale Boost

Pounce.Description: Instant: The hunter engages in limited flight, zooming ahead and damaging enemies in his path for 50 damage.
Pounce.Name: Glide Strike

Rage.Description: Instant: Sends the savage into a reckless rage for 12.5 seconds, decreasing armor by 50%%, increasing damage by 25%%.
Rage.Name: Rage

Reconstitute.Description: Instant: The legionnaire reconstitutes his body for 20 seconds. While in this state, the legionnaire's health regeneration rate is increased by 150%%.
Reconstitute.Name: Reconstitute

Riposte.Description: Instant: Activates riposte for 20 seconds. While riposte is active, the legionnaire receives 2 additional armor and 25%% of all melee damage delt to the legionnaire is returned to its attackers.
Riposte.Name: Riposte

Sacrifice.Description: Instant: The shapeshifter sacrifices himself, reducing armor by 25%%, speed by 15%%, and stamina regeneration by 25%%. After 18 seconds, he explodes, dealing 1700 base damage to structures and units in a small radius.
Sacrifice.Name: Sacrifice

Sentry.Description: Gadget: Places a Sentry Bat on the ground that lasts for 5 minutes and reveals enemy units, including ones who are polymorphed or cloaked. The user is rewarded with experience for how effective the bat is at scouting the battlefield.
Sentry.Name: Eyes of the Bat

ShieldGenerator.Description: Gadget: Places a shield generator on the field that lasts for 30 seconds. Any units inside the shield generator are completely protected from ranged attacks .
ShieldGenerator.Name: Shield Generator

Shockwave.Description: Instant: Activates a shockwave that deals 150-190 damage to opponents.
Shockwave.Name: Shockwave

Sleep.Description: Self Buff: The hunter goes into a deep sleep. Protected by his wings, he is immune to ranged attack and heals over time.
Sleep.Name: Hibernate

SolProtection.Description: Self Buff: The chaplain is protected by the power of Sol, becoming immune to damage for 8 seconds. Additionally, 40%% of any damage caused will heal the chaplain.
SolProtection.Name: Shield of Sol

Stealth.Description: Instant: The scout slips into stealth for 45 seconds. Any attacks will remove the scout from stealth. Any damage received will remove the scout from stealth. Demo charges and other gadgets may be placed without breaking stealth.
Stealth.Name: Vanish

SteamBoost.Description: Instant: Activates steam boost for 10 seconds. While steam boost is active, the siege unit travels 80%% faster.
SteamBoost.Name: Steam Boost

Stomp.Description: Instant: The behemoth stomps his foot, dealing 150-175 damage to nearby enemies and stunning them for 2.5 seconds.
Stomp.Name: Stomp

SummonMole.Description: The familiar helpers of Conjurers, highly intelligent Moles are summoned to repair structures damaged in battle.
SummonMole.Name: Summon Mole

TephraWave.Description: Instant: Spews forth fire from the malphas, dealing 200-225 damage to enemies that are caught within the flames.
TephraWave.Name: Tephra Wave

TrunkSlam.Description: Instant: The behemoth slams his tree trunk into the ground, doing 225-250 damage to enemy units.
TrunkSlam.Name: Trunk Slam

Venomous.Description: Instant: The predator lunges forward with a fiery claw, dealing 70-85 damage, increasing his attack speed by 20%% for 2 seconds and setting his target on fire for a short time.
Venomous.Name: Fiery Strike

Vomit.Description: Instant: The devourer vomits. Any players hit by the attack will take 125-140 damage and have their armor reduced to 50% of normal and take 7 damage per second for 10 seconds.
Vomit.Name: Vomit

WhirlingBlade.Description: Instant: The legionnaire does a 360 attack dealing 105-120 damage to nearby enemies and interrupts any action they are currently performing.
WhirlingBlade.Name: Whirling Blade

WingSpin.Description: Instant: The Hunter spins for 3 seconds while performing 6 attacks of 65 damage each to all nearby opponents. The hunter is also immune to ranged damage, moves at 70% of normal speed, and has slightly increased armor while spinning.
WingSpin.Name: Wing Spin

Atrophy.Description: Area of Effect: Enemies within the target area have their armor reduced by 6 for 20 seconds.
Atrophy.Name: Atrophy

Attrition.Description: Snapcast: Target enemy has their armor reduced by 75%% for 20 seconds.
Attrition.Name: Will of God

BeastHeal.Description: Snapcast: Heal a target ally for 120 health over 3 seconds.
BeastHeal.Name: Reinvigorate

BladeFlame.Description: Melee mode: Embues Maliken's blade with fire. Each successful melee hit applies a fire damage over time to a target. This effect stacks with each melee hit
BladeFlame.Name: Blade of Flames

BladeHealing.Description: Melee mode: Each successful melee attack will heal nearby allies based on the damage done to an opponent
BladeHealing.Name: Blade of Healing

BladeLightning.Description: Melee mode: Each successful melee attack will cause a bolt of lightning to jump from your primary target to nearby enemies
BladeLightning.Name: Blade of Lightning

BladeWind.Description: Melee mode: Melee attacks stir up a gust of wind which protect maliken from ranged attacks.
BladeWind.Name: Blade of Wind

Combustion.Description: Snapcast: Calling forth Hellfire, Combustion sets the target enemy on fire for 10 seconds. While burning, target takes 35 damage per second.
Combustion.Name: Combustion

CommanderCenturionArmor.Description: Gives allied units in an area 6 bonus armor for 20 seconds.
CommanderCenturionArmor.Name: Centurion Armor

CommanderCripple.Description: Decreases enemy movement speed by 35%% for 15 seconds.
CommanderCripple.Name: Cripple

CommanderDispel.Description: Removes all buffs and debuffs from targeted unit.
CommanderDispel.Name: Dispel

CommanderFear.Description: Reduces enemy units armor by 7 in an area for 15 seconds.
CommanderFear.Name: Piercing Fear

CommanderHeal.Description: Heals targeted ally unit for 120 hp over 10 seconds.
CommanderHeal.Name: Heal

CommanderLifeLeak.Description: Slowly damages the targeted enemy unit by 7.5 hp/sec for 20 seconds.
CommanderLifeLeak.Name: Life Leak

CommanderRecall.Description: Allows targeted unit to teleport back to base.
CommanderRecall.Name: Recall

CommanderResurrect.Description: Bring a fallen soldier back to life.
CommanderResurrect.Name: Resurrect

CommanderReveal.Description: Use this spell to see hidden areas of the map to check for sneak attacks and bases.
CommanderReveal.Name: Reveal Fog of War

CommanderSpeedBoost.Description: Increases targeted allied units movement speed by 30%% for 15 seconds.
CommanderSpeedBoost.Name: Speed Boost

ConsumeCorpse.Description: Snapcast: The devourer consumes an enemy corpse. Enemy player becomes unrevivable. With each corpse the devourer's health, health regen, and damage increase by 25%%, maximum benefit is 75%%. With each level devourer's size increased by 20%%. The buff effects decrease over time.
ConsumeCorpse.Name: Devour Corpse

Decay.Description: Self Buff: The devourer releases a gas over time, doing 25 damage per second to enemies in an area around him.
Decay.Name: Rot

Defile.Description: Snapcast: Deals 350 damage to target enemy.
Defile.Name: Defile

Enchant.Description: A weaker, but broader emanation of the power Summoners have over lesser creatures enables them to Enchant hostile beings with wills weaker than their own.
Enchant.Name: Enchant

Entangle.Description: Snapcast: Roots target enemy in place for 3.5 seconds. The target is set free sooner if he receives more than 50 damage.
Entangle.Name: Entangle

EntangleTrap.Description: Area of Effect: Enemies within the radius of this spell are rooted in place for 2.5 seconds. The targets are set free sooner if they receive more than 50 damage.
EntangleTrap.Name: Entangle Trap

Eruption.Description: Area of Effect: Malphas summons an eruption in the target area that deals 200 damage and stuns enemies for 1.8 seconds.
Eruption.Name: Eruption

Fear.Description: Area of Effect: Enemies within a large radius around the predator are filled with fear for 12.5 seconds. While afraid, enemies have their armor reduced by 75%%.
Fear.Name: Fear

Grenade.Description: A wise Builder keeps a few of Grenades filled with potent concoction of alchemic ingredients in case the situation calls for an explosive solution.
Grenade.Name: Grenade

GroupHeal.Description: Area of Effect: Allies within the radius of the group heal spell are healed for 75 health over 1 second.
GroupHeal.Name: Group Heal

HailStorm.Description: Calling on the powers of the heavens, Tempests unleashing Hail Storms raining icy blocks the size of fists that wreak havoc on any foes caught within range.
HailStorm.Name: Hail Storm

Heal.Description: Snapcast: Heal target ally for 138 health over 2 seconds.
Heal.Name: Heal

HealPet.Description: Snapcast: Heal target pet for 105 over 1.5 seconds. This spell works on allied pets as well as your own.
HealPet.Name: Heal Pet

ManaFountain.Description: Gadget: Places a mana fountain on the field for 30 seconds that restores 50%% of a player's maximum mana when used. The conjurer who places the mana well is awarded 25 experience for each player who uses it.
ManaFountain.Name: Mana Fountain

Meteor.Description: Area of Effect: The Tempest summon a meteor down from the skies, dealing 950 base damage to enemy structures in a small radius.
Meteor.Name: Meteor Strike

MindWarp.Description: Snapcast: The shaman warps the target enemy's mind for 4 seconds. While mind warped, target player cannot use any skills or abilities, has a highly distorted view and movement speed is reduced by 33%%.
MindWarp.Name: Mind Warp

Mortification.Description: Snapcast: Slows target enemy's movement speed by 60%% for 10 seconds.
Mortification.Name: Mortification

Polymorph.Description: Snapcast: Transform yourself to appear as an enemy unit for 45 seconds at an additional cost of 3 mana per second. You will appear as an ally to your enemies and be able to be targeted by their friendly spells.
Polymorph.Name: Polymorph

RainOfFire.Description: AoE Spell that calls down hellfire onto an area causing enemies to burn.
RainOfFire.Name: Rain Of Fire

Reincarnate.Description: Snapcast: Resurrect target ally who recently died with half health and half mana. If target has returned to the loadout screen you will not be able to revive him.
Reincarnate.Name: Reincarnate

Resurrect.Description: Snapcast: Resurrect target ally who recently died with half health and half mana. If target has returned to the loadout screen you will not be able to revive him.
Resurrect.Name: Resurrect

SteamTurret.Description: Gadget: Places a steam turret with 350 health that will shoot at enemies for 20 seconds.
SteamTurret.Name: Steam Turret

StormShield.Description: Snapcast: Protects target ally from all ranged damage for 12 seconds.
StormShield.Name: Storm Shield

SummonBearloth.Description: Pet: Summons a bearloth to fight for you. The bearloth has 525 health, 10 armor, and can perform all the basic melee attacks. Summoning a new pet will destroy your previous pet.
SummonBearloth.Name: Summon Bearloth

SummonImp.Description: Pet: Summons an imp to fight for you. The imp has 425 health, 3 armor, and uses a ranged attack that deals 35-45 damage. Summoning a new pet will destroy your previous pet.
SummonImp.Name: Summon Imp

Venus.Description: Gadget: Places a poisonous venus plant with 400 health on the field that will shoot at enemies for 20 seconds.
Venus.Name: Poisonous Venus

CommanderRecall.GameTip: Recall has been cast upon you. To be recalled to a spawn point, press the use (E) key within 10 seconds.
CommanderRecall.Name: Commander Recall

Rot.Description: Flesh eating bacteria begins to eat away at the skin from the vile rotten flesh that has made contact with the bearer of this state.
Rot.Name: Rot

SavioursValor.GameTip: You have used Saviour's Valor. You are being recalled to a spawn point.
SavioursValor.Name: Savior's Valor

Spawned.GameTip: You may press the ^gY^w key to view a description of your abilities
Spawned.Name: NAME
